00:00:18,958 --> 00:00:20,666
♪

4
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:26,000
♪

5
00:00:29,458 --> 00:00:31,666
♪

6
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,416
♪

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,958
♪

8
00:00:43,416 --> 00:00:45,125
♪

9
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,666
♪

10
00:00:54,666 --> 00:00:56,583
♪

11
00:00:56,666 --> 00:00:58,208
[sighs]

12
00:00:58,291 --> 00:01:01,958
♪

13
00:01:02,041 --> 00:01:03,166
Are you watching?

14
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:05,416
I've come a long way already.

15
00:01:06,416 --> 00:01:08,416
I just know I'll win
the Inter High.

16
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,416
♪

17
00:01:12,708 --> 00:01:14,666
[CROWD cheering]

18
00:01:17,708 --> 00:01:19,500
[grunts]

19
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:20,833
That's three!

20
00:01:20,916 --> 00:01:22,416
Which means he's won
enough individual bouts

21
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:23,500
now to qualify!

22
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:25,625
He's in top form today.

23
00:01:25,708 --> 00:01:27,375
As expected.

24
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:29,750
So Onimaru's back, huh?

25
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:32,750
Seems he really did invest
three years into training.

26
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:35,000
His patience is admirable.

27
00:01:35,083 --> 00:01:38,666
But he won't beat me as long
as he has that look on his face.

28
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,916
Then again, he's not
the only one aiming to.

29
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:45,666
Time to meet my challengers
in the ring and defend my title.

30
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:47,666
♪

31
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:50,000
[ANNOUNCER]
On the west side, Hayashi.

32
00:01:50,083 --> 00:01:53,500
On the east side, Tennoji.

33
00:01:53,583 --> 00:01:56,875
[breathing heavily]

34
00:01:56,958 --> 00:01:58,291
♪

35
00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:04,125
-[REFEREE] Spirit!
-[HAYASHI grunts]

36
00:02:07,708 --> 00:02:09,416
[REFEREE]
The bout is decided!

37
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,083
East side wins!

38
00:02:11,166 --> 00:02:12,458
[CROWD murmuring]

39
00:02:12,541 --> 00:02:14,125
[scoffs]
I'm going to enjoy

40
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:16,166
putting an end
to Hakuro's reign.

41
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:18,333
What do you think?
Can you beat him, Sosuke?

42
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:21,708
If I had any doubt,
I wouldn't be here.

43
00:02:23,166 --> 00:02:26,458
[KIRIHITO] Shido Tennoji,
from Tottori Hakuro.

44
00:02:26,541 --> 00:02:28,833
The reigning champ
of high school sumo.

45
00:02:29,958 --> 00:02:31,541
I didn't think we'd draw him
this early on

46
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:32,875
in the competition.

47
00:02:32,958 --> 00:02:35,333
It's a tough match
right out of the gate.

48
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:37,041
You make it out to sound
like a bad thing,

49
00:02:37,125 --> 00:02:38,583
but it suits me just fine.

50
00:02:39,583 --> 00:02:41,500
The whole reason I'm here
is to upset the odds

51
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:42,958
and do the impossible.

52
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,458
I'll bring down Tennoji and show
everyone what I already know.

53
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,333
That there's another
incredible fighter here today!

54
00:04:23,541 --> 00:04:25,666
[TENNOJI]
What do I think of Ushio?

55
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,458
He's got strength.

56
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:28,875
And I have nothing
but admiration

57
00:04:28,958 --> 00:04:30,208
for the guy making it this far,

58
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:32,500
considering the body
he was stuck with.

59
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:35,041
Looking at me now,
you would have never guessed,

60
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:37,500
but I used to be
quite small myself.

61
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:39,666
I'm the only one
in my family who isn't.

62
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:42,375
I'm truly thankful
to the sumo gods for blessing me

63
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:43,708
with this physique.

64
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:47,791
-[HINOMARU]] Ready!
-[CHIHIRO] Hinomaru!

65
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:49,958
I know there's no reason
to tell you this

66
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:52,791
and you already know it,
but I'm gonna say it anyway.

67
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:56,916
Win this, go out there and
become the high school yokozuna!

68
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,916
I will!

69
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,333
[KIRIHITO]
This is it.

70
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:02,375
Your admission to the pro league
is on the line.

71
00:05:03,375 --> 00:05:04,833
[HINOMARU] Tennoji's someone
I've always had

72
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:06,541
immense respect for.

73
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:09,041
He was both the middle
and high school yokozuna.

74
00:05:10,416 --> 00:05:12,666
I get to fight someone who's
already walked down the path

75
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:14,250
I'm traveling.

76
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:16,666
[ANNOUNCER]
On the east side, Ushio.

77
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,208
On the west side, Tennoji.

78
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:21,458
[HINOMARU]
Today, I defeat the champion

79
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:22,791
and take the crown.

80
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,375
Their spirits are so intense,

81
00:05:27,458 --> 00:05:29,291
you can feel them
on the second floor.

82
00:05:29,375 --> 00:05:30,791
When I imagine
what it's like in the ring,

83
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:32,750
it sends chills down my spine.

84
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,833
[SHUNKAI] He truly is
the yokozuna of this space.

85
00:05:35,916 --> 00:05:38,375
An opponent with even
the slightest bit of uncertainty

86
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:39,708
would be engulfed
by his aura

87
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:41,625
and unable to fight
to their full ability.

88
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:46,250
However, that's only true
for the weak-spirited.

89
00:05:47,583 --> 00:05:49,791
With the confidence
and resolve Hinomaru's

90
00:05:49,875 --> 00:05:52,000
been steadily building
for this day,

91
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:54,500
he can take on even a yokozuna.

92
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:56,583
♪

93
00:05:58,583 --> 00:06:00,541
♪

94
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:04,958
♪

95
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:08,583
♪

96
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:14,166
-[REFEREE] Spirit!
-[HINOMARU grunts]

97
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,750
He used a forearm charge?

98
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:20,000
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
He struck him despite

99
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:21,958
his low stance and speed?

100
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:24,625
[SAENOYAMA]
He's fast.

101
00:06:24,708 --> 00:06:26,125
Went from a wild forearm charge

102
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:28,125
to a precise grapple
like it was nothing.

103
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:29,500
[BATO]
No surprise.

104
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:31,833
The boss built up momentum
from the get-go.

105
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:34,583
[ENOKI] It's the captain's first
time fighting someone so short,

106
00:06:34,666 --> 00:06:36,916
but he didn't hesitate
for a second.

107
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:42,000
[SHUNKAI] He knew the
exact moment to grab his belt.

108
00:06:42,083 --> 00:06:43,625
It's not just his stature.

109
00:06:43,708 --> 00:06:45,833
His skill's equally impressive.

110
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:47,375
[KIRIHITO]
Shido Tennoji.

111
00:06:47,458 --> 00:06:49,583
Measuring at 188 centimeters,

112
00:06:49,666 --> 00:06:51,583
he's been blessed with size.

113
00:06:51,666 --> 00:06:53,041
But in elementary school,

114
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:54,916
he wasn't considered
imposing at all.

115
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,208
You can't predict
when your growth spurt will hit

116
00:06:58,291 --> 00:06:59,833
or to what extent.

117
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:01,750
So he trained in techniques
that would help him survive

118
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,875
against larger sumos.

119
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:05,833
The road that Hinomaru is on,

120
00:07:05,916 --> 00:07:07,541
Tennoji knows all too well.

121
00:07:08,583 --> 00:07:10,833
But now, looking back
at what he went through,

122
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:13,291
it's almost as if the path
he traveled was laid out

123
00:07:13,375 --> 00:07:14,625
by the sumo gods to make him

124
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,375
the strongest wrestler
in history.

125
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:19,708
As though they picked him
out of the crowd and said,

126
00:07:19,791 --> 00:07:22,291
"You. Enter the ring."

127
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:23,375
[TENNOJI smirks]

128
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:27,625
[HINOMARU straining]

129
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:30,583
You should know by now,
sumo gods.

130
00:07:30,666 --> 00:07:33,666
Whatever ordeal you put me
through, I won't stop!

131
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,333
Stay out of this!

132
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,500
[TENMA]
Onimaru has speed on his side.

133
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:43,000
And power too.

134
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:44,625
But that's not all.

135
00:07:44,708 --> 00:07:47,458
He can shield his own belt
and seize his opponent's.

136
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:49,333
He's been the same height
for so long,

137
00:07:49,416 --> 00:07:52,083
he's perfected
the art of blocking grabs.

138
00:07:52,166 --> 00:07:53,750
And then counterattacking.

139
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:57,166
[HINOMARU] You'll never take
this away from me!

140
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,375
You listening?

141
00:07:58,458 --> 00:07:59,916
I love it too much!

142
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:02,083
[REINA]
Shorty's got the edge!

143
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:03,625
No! Not yet!

144
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:08,625
[TENNOJI]
I've studied your moves, Ushio,

145
00:08:08,708 --> 00:08:10,875
and I know all about
your counterattack.

146
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,291
Not only that.

147
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:13,833
I'm aware
its main purpose is to get

148
00:08:13,916 --> 00:08:15,666
a firm grip
with your right hand.

149
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:16,875
The left doesn't matter.

150
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:18,833
So, by sealing off your grab,

151
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:20,916
I can cut
your offensive power in half.

152
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:26,166
-He's throwing him!
-And it's working!

153
00:08:26,250 --> 00:08:27,625
[TENNOJI]
I see.

154
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:29,916
Trying to create an opening
for your right hand.

155
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,166
[HINOMARU]
Damn! In that case.

156
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:34,000
[TENNOJI] Quick as a flash,
you'll change it up

157
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:35,833
and go
for throat strikes instead.

158
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,750
There.

159
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,291
There's nothing you can do
I haven't predicted.

160
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:45,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA] He's not reacting
to incoming moves.

161
00:08:45,666 --> 00:08:48,208
He's anticipating them
before they even happen.

162
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:51,625
Say what you will,
but he's done his homework.

163
00:08:51,708 --> 00:08:54,458
[SAKI] My brother studied
every wrestler here.

164
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:56,000
[TENNOJI]
Tsuyoshi Kanamori.

165
00:08:56,083 --> 00:08:58,000
He's hard to shift
once he buckles down,

166
00:08:58,083 --> 00:09:00,458
but he can't react
to a fast attack.

167
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:03,125
Even on your time off,
you're watching sumo.

168
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:05,375
[TENNOJI laughs]
It's my hobby.

169
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:08,458
I enjoy studying
all different styles of sumo.

170
00:09:08,541 --> 00:09:11,041
Besides, a yokozuna
can still fall to wrestlers

171
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:13,000
who're lower in rank than he is.

172
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:15,833
If I'm prepared,

173
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,791
I can't lose.

174
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,208
[KIRIHITO]
He knows about the pressure

175
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:20,583
of defending a title.

176
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,208
That's why he keeps
his ego in check

177
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:24,833
and always researches opponents
before a match.

178
00:09:24,916 --> 00:09:27,416
As a result,
he's never lost a bout.

179
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:30,750
Not once his entire time
in high school.

180
00:09:32,541 --> 00:09:34,000
He's feeling the strain now.

181
00:09:34,083 --> 00:09:36,750
Grappling with somebody
twice your size can't be easy.

182
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,500
[BATO]
This guy's not so tough.

183
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:42,291
[TENNOJI]
You're breathing hard.

184
00:09:42,375 --> 00:09:43,833
Having a rough time, Ushio?

185
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,625
[breathing heavily]

186
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:47,666
[TENNOJI]
You poor creature.

187
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:50,250
There isn't another sumo
wrestler your size out there

188
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:51,958
who can match your talent.

189
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:54,291
But surely you noticed by now.

190
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,166
No other sumo wrestler
is suffering

191
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:57,625
as intensely as you are.

192
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:00,208
Let's get this over with.

193
00:10:02,041 --> 00:10:03,875
It's too painful to watch!

194
00:10:05,708 --> 00:10:08,166
He doesn't understand
the first thing about Hinomaru.

195
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:10,000
[HINOMARU grunts]

196
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:12,625
[ALL gasp]

197
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:15,291
[KIRIHITO] You said that you
love sumo more than anyone else.

198
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:16,750
It's no secret.

199
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,291
But I wonder.

200
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:20,125
Has anyone ever called you
on that statement before?

201
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:21,750
♪

202
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,416
[HINOMARU grunts]

203
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:26,500
[HINOMARU] Preparing for this
day has been several things.

204
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:27,666
Difficult.

205
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:28,750
Painful.

206
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,166
Discouraging.

207
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:31,916
But whatever I encountered,

208
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,708
I never got burnt out on sumo!

209
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:34,708
Not even once!

210
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:36,291
♪

211
00:10:38,041 --> 00:10:40,458
[HINOMARU]
No one loves it more than me!

212
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:42,500
Including you!

213
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:48,583
[ALL gasp]

214
00:10:48,666 --> 00:10:49,958
[TENNOJI]
Onimaru.

215
00:10:50,041 --> 00:10:52,750
I can see the flames
on your back.

216
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,375
[YUMA]
A double-handed grip!

217
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:58,875
[SHIBAKIYAMA] He's readying
the Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop!

218
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:01,875
You spent too much time
testing the waters, Tennoji.

219
00:11:01,958 --> 00:11:05,250
Once Onimaru's in that position,
it only means one thing.

220
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,541
Trouble.

221
00:11:06,625 --> 00:11:08,041
[SHUNKAI]
He needs to get him off-balance

222
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:09,833
before executing the technique.

223
00:11:10,916 --> 00:11:13,166
Fortunately, he's learned
there are infinite ways

224
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,250
to set up his opponent.

225
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:16,041
♪

226
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,208
[HINOMARU] Rock him back
and forth, left and right!

227
00:11:19,208 --> 00:11:21,708
Don't stop!
Not until he loses his balance!

228
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:25,166
Two-Handed Demon Storm!

229
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,166
Hmm?

230
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:28,666
♪

231
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:30,041
[grunts]

232
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:32,041
A sideways jerk!

233
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:34,458
[TENMA]
Yanking him back and forth.

234
00:11:34,541 --> 00:11:37,083
He used the same technique
in Nagoya.

235
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:39,458
I doubt there's footage
of it though.

236
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:41,333
Before, he'd go straight
from that stance

237
00:11:41,416 --> 00:11:43,750
into the
Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop.

238
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:47,166
There's no reason to be scared
of one-shot techniques.

239
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:50,541
But if he's willing to use
a powerhouse move

240
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:52,541
like that as a setup,

241
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:53,833
one thing's for sure.

242
00:11:54,958 --> 00:11:56,625
Even you'll have trouble
anticipating

243
00:11:56,708 --> 00:11:59,458
what his next plan
of attack will be, Tennoji.

244
00:12:02,375 --> 00:12:04,416
[SAENOYAMA] Maybe facing off
against him this early on

245
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,750
was a good thing.

246
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,125
If it'd been any later,

247
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:09,000
Ushio would've already
showed his hand by now

248
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:11,208
and wouldn't have been
in peak physical condition.

249
00:12:12,791 --> 00:12:14,083
He caught me with my guard down

250
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:16,000
several times
in the training hall.

251
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:17,375
Once he's in that stance,

252
00:12:17,458 --> 00:12:19,166
even a pro would have
difficulty escaping.

253
00:12:21,041 --> 00:12:23,000
-He grabbed on!
-Damn, brute-force!

254
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:25,958
He's still flinging him around!

255
00:12:26,041 --> 00:12:27,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Go!

256
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:29,458
He doesn't have enough arm
strength to stop your twists!

257
00:12:29,541 --> 00:12:31,458
Create a bigger whirlpool.

258
00:12:31,541 --> 00:12:33,416
And suck Tennoji in!

259
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,416
-Now's his chance!
-Finish him!

260
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,916
♪

261
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,166
[TENNOJI]
Hundred Demon Takedown.

262
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,625
[ALL gasp]

263
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,708
-There's no way!
-Hinomaru's technique!

264
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:55,291
Hundred Demon Takedown!

265
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:58,833
It's weird seeing someone taller
than Onimaru using his move.

266
00:12:58,916 --> 00:13:01,291
Like it's ten times
more powerful than usual.

267
00:13:02,291 --> 00:13:04,958
[SHIBAKIYAMA] He was biding his
time, waiting for an opening.

268
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:08,083
No one but a champ counters
one throw with another!

269
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:10,458
[TENNOJI] So this is
your new style of sumo?

270
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:13,041
Impressive.

271
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,250
Seems those three
difficult years of middle school

272
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:17,791
provided you with more
than just pain.

273
00:13:17,875 --> 00:13:20,500
Goes to show I don't know
everything about this sport.

274
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:22,833
And the fire burning inside
those who practice it!

275
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:24,333
[HINOMARU grunts]

276
00:13:27,208 --> 00:13:28,625
Not yet.

277
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:29,750
It isn't over!

278
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:35,041
[HINOMARU] You're even stronger
than I imagined, Tennoji.

279
00:13:35,125 --> 00:13:36,958
I've always respected
your strength.

280
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:38,958
♪

281
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:40,708
The first time I saw you fight,

282
00:13:40,791 --> 00:13:42,666
it was forever seared
into my mind.

283
00:13:43,708 --> 00:13:44,958
Even though you were small,

284
00:13:45,041 --> 00:13:46,791
you were so powerful.

285
00:13:47,791 --> 00:13:49,541
I watched your bout
over and over

286
00:13:49,625 --> 00:13:52,000
to the point
I started dreaming about it.

287
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:55,500
Everyone around me
had gotten bigger.

288
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:57,333
Even if I wasn't winning,

289
00:13:57,416 --> 00:14:00,000
watching you that day
made me feel like a giant.

290
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:03,708
You showed me even guys
our size can win.

291
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:07,208
You may have grown,
but you're still the fighter

292
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:09,375
I measure myself against.

293
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:11,958
The wrestler at the summit
I have to defeat!

294
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:13,666
♪

295
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:14,791
[grunts]

296
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:19,916
[ALL gasp]

297
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,416
[HINOMARU]
Incredible.

298
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:25,375
Which makes me want
to beat you even more!

299
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:26,541
[KARIYA]
There's the opening!

300
00:14:26,625 --> 00:14:28,000
[KUZE]
He's pushing.

301
00:14:28,083 --> 00:14:30,583
[SHUNKAI] He was expecting
to avoid a throw,

302
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:32,833
and the little demon
took advantage of it.

303
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:35,583
[HINOMARU] I've spent
enough time admiring your sumo.

304
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:39,208
I've got one last technique
to unbalance you!

305
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:40,916
[KUZE]
It was a bluff.

306
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:44,416
Tennoji resisted by moving
his weight forward.

307
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,166
Now, he can land it.

308
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,166
Go.

309
00:14:47,250 --> 00:14:48,708
Go!

310
00:14:53,125 --> 00:14:54,041
[ALL gasp]

311
00:14:54,125 --> 00:14:55,083
Whoa!

312
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,958
He broke free!

313
00:14:59,041 --> 00:15:00,875
[SAENOYAMA]
How could he evade it?

314
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:03,666
He wasn't using all his strength
against the push.

315
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:06,666
Tennoji kept some in reserve
to counter the next move.

316
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:09,500
[SAKI]
Ushio executed a perfect attack.

317
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:10,791
Unfortunately for him,

318
00:15:10,875 --> 00:15:13,791
my brother's love for sumo
is more intense.

319
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:16,791
He uncovers all the info he can
on potential challengers

320
00:15:16,875 --> 00:15:18,750
and pores over it.

321
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:20,500
But that's not
his only strategy.

322
00:15:21,708 --> 00:15:24,166
He envisions
all possible scenarios.

323
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:25,625
Every play they'll make.

324
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:27,541
All the ways
he could lose to them.

325
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,125
Rocking side-to-side,
exchanging blows,

326
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:33,458
then a push followed
by his triple combo.

327
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:35,541
That should've meant
victory for Ushio.

328
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:36,791
One problem.

329
00:15:36,875 --> 00:15:39,041
My brother already
anticipated it

330
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:40,875
and came up with a counter!

331
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:43,458
[TENNOJI]
He's a fearsome adversary.

332
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:45,375
Whenever I imagine my opponents,

333
00:15:45,458 --> 00:15:48,708
I build them up to be
something larger than life.

334
00:15:48,791 --> 00:15:50,375
Usually,
the worst-case scenarios

335
00:15:50,458 --> 00:15:53,166
I base my strategies around
are unrealistic.

336
00:15:54,291 --> 00:15:55,750
Usually.

337
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:58,750
But not with you, Onimaru.

338
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,708
Your blade was pressed
against my throat.

339
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,916
I used to be small, same as you.

340
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,750
Right up until my first year
of middle school.

341
00:16:09,833 --> 00:16:12,666
I barely avoided wandering
that merciless hell

342
00:16:12,750 --> 00:16:15,083
you've lived through
these last several years.

343
00:16:15,166 --> 00:16:17,083
But you made it
to the other side.

344
00:16:17,166 --> 00:16:18,833
And here you stand.

345
00:16:18,916 --> 00:16:20,375
I'm in awe of you!

346
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,416
The problem is
you're wound up too tight.

347
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:26,500
You want to be a yokozuna,
don't you?

348
00:16:26,583 --> 00:16:28,541
The absolute best of the best.

349
00:16:28,625 --> 00:16:31,583
If that's your goal, try
to enjoy bouts a little more!

350
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:34,458
♪

351
00:16:34,541 --> 00:16:37,416
If sumo's your life
and you love it,

352
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,166
then no matter
what setbacks you face,

353
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:41,083
there's only one thing
you can do.

354
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:43,291
You have to smile!

355
00:16:43,375 --> 00:16:45,041
Six Point Torso Slice!

356
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:47,375
[CHIZUKO/REINA gasp]

357
00:16:47,458 --> 00:16:48,958
♪

358
00:16:51,958 --> 00:16:53,458
♪

359
00:16:54,958 --> 00:16:56,833
[straining]

360
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:59,291
♪

361
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:00,791
[TENNOJI] What's with
that look in his eye?

362
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:03,375
One last desperate act?

363
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:09,083
Thought so.
I expected nothing less.

364
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:11,125
♪

365
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:15,583
[TENNOJI] That's what makes you
so damn cool!

366
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:17,541
[strains]

367
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:35,708
The west side wins.

368
00:17:35,791 --> 00:17:38,541
Tennoji is victorious
with an arm-lock throw.

369
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,750
[CROWD cheering]

370
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,750
[TENNOJI] You've given me plenty
to think about, Onimaru.

371
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:56,541
I won't be celebrating
this victory.

372
00:17:57,833 --> 00:18:00,291
Not out of gratitude
or enlightenment,

373
00:18:00,375 --> 00:18:02,083
but respect for your style.

374
00:18:05,208 --> 00:18:08,208
[REINA] Since he doesn't meet
the minimum height requirements,

375
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:10,750
his only shot at getting
into the pro league

376
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:12,625
was to become
a high school yokozuna

377
00:18:12,708 --> 00:18:14,375
here at the Inter High.

378
00:18:14,458 --> 00:18:15,583
After that, he could enter

379
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:18,166
the All-Japan
National Championships.

380
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:20,750
And now, that path is closed.

381
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:21,958
It's over.

382
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:26,500
Well, guess I lost!

383
00:18:26,583 --> 00:18:28,125
Dude was really strong,
wasn't he?

384
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:30,375
[HINOMARU laughs]

385
00:18:30,458 --> 00:18:32,000
No use crying over spilled milk.

386
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:34,083
We got the team tournament
up next.

387
00:18:34,166 --> 00:18:35,708
Just gotta shake it off.

388
00:18:35,791 --> 00:18:38,291
Besides, I'm only a first year.

389
00:18:38,375 --> 00:18:41,166
There'll be other chances for me
to join the pro league.

390
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:42,541
[REINA]
It won't be the same.

391
00:18:42,625 --> 00:18:44,583
Tennoji will have graduated.

392
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:46,916
All the work you put in
was so you could beat him.

393
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:51,125
So, for the team matches,
what's the order?

394
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:52,500
Where's Kirihito?

395
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:54,666
You don't need to fight
in the team tournament.

396
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:55,833
Huh?

397
00:18:57,875 --> 00:19:00,291
-Captain.
-Why not?

398
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:01,750
Sorry?

399
00:19:01,833 --> 00:19:03,916
[OZEKI] We talked it over
and came to a decision.

400
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:06,250
[grunts]

401
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,208
[OZEKI]
Just as I thought.

402
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:09,708
We're you planning
on telling us?

403
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,250
[HINOMARU] I'm perfectly fine!
This is nothing!

404
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:15,958
Tsuji's calling for a taxi
to come pick you up.

405
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:18,083
Then you're going
to the hospital.

406
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:20,083
Did you forget
about our promise?

407
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:22,000
We're making Dachi High
the best in Japan!

408
00:19:22,083 --> 00:19:23,166
Hey!

409
00:19:24,291 --> 00:19:26,583
The individual tournament,
getting into the pro league,

410
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:28,041
that was my mountain
to climb!

411
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:31,625
But... Dachi High winning,

412
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:34,500
we all dreamed
of making that happen!

413
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:36,041
What about you?

414
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:37,541
And Yuma?

415
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:39,583
This is the only year
you'll be on the team.

416
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:40,875
Don't take this away.

417
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:42,375
Please, let me help!

418
00:19:43,583 --> 00:19:46,416
I want to make at least
one dream become a reality!

419
00:19:50,583 --> 00:19:51,708
I'm sorry.

420
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:55,333
[OZEKI]
You don't need to apologize.

421
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:57,708
Just get ready for the bouts
tomorrow and the day after.

422
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:01,166
You're not done, Ushio.

423
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,958
Your dream of joining
the pro league isn't over.

424
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:06,666
Not as long as the team
tournament's still up for grabs.

425
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:08,666
-[shudders]
-[REINA] Huh?

426
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:11,291
Wait. I thought Shorty had
to win his match.

427
00:20:11,375 --> 00:20:13,375
That was the only way
he could become a yokozuna

428
00:20:13,458 --> 00:20:15,125
and get a spot
at the nationals.

429
00:20:15,208 --> 00:20:17,333
Well, that's how
it usually works.

430
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:19,791
But more than one
can earn that title.

431
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:20,916
Huh?

432
00:20:22,291 --> 00:20:25,458
[OZEKI] For the past two years,
Tennoji has had so much success,

433
00:20:25,541 --> 00:20:27,583
he was the only one
given the honor.

434
00:20:27,666 --> 00:20:29,250
Before him though,
there were two,

435
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:31,250
sometimes three
who received the mantle.

436
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:34,125
Okay, but at the pace
he's been going,

437
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,791
he's probably gonna be
the only one selected again.

438
00:20:36,875 --> 00:20:38,166
Look. Sure.

439
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:40,625
We know Shido Tennoji
has been unstoppable.

440
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:42,458
But if he had his first defeat,

441
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:44,916
it wouldn't matter if it was
during the team tournament.

442
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,750
♪

443
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:49,083
Yeah, but there's no guarantee
it'll work though.

444
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:51,541
Tottori Hakuro might lose
to some other school's team

445
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,083
before we even draw them.

446
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:54,833
[OZEKI]
Okay! Maybe!

447
00:20:54,916 --> 00:20:56,791
Then we'll just take down
whichever one beats Tennoji!

448
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:59,791
Anyway, that's the strategy.

449
00:20:59,875 --> 00:21:02,750
I know it's got a slim chance
of working,

450
00:21:02,833 --> 00:21:05,166
but it's the only one we got,
so we have to try.

451
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:06,791
♪

452
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:08,625
The master knows a good doc.

453
00:21:08,708 --> 00:21:10,791
They should get you
fixed up in no time.

454
00:21:12,041 --> 00:21:14,250
While you're healing,
we'll make sure to survive

455
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,458
the team competition.

456
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:18,166
You said getting to
the professional league

457
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:20,125
was your mountain to climb,

458
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,833
but from now on,
it's also our dream.

459
00:21:22,916 --> 00:21:25,250
You want to be
the strongest high school sumo?

460
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:27,291
We'll work to give you
another shot at it.

461
00:21:27,375 --> 00:21:29,833
Show off. Let us carry
some of the weight too.

462
00:21:29,916 --> 00:21:32,208
You can count on it.
We got this.

463
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:33,416
Yeah, piece of cake!

464
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,916
[OZEKI]
Let's do it, Ushio.

465
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,291
We're gonna win again and again
and keep winning

466
00:21:38,375 --> 00:21:40,125
until those big shots
finally take notice

467
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:42,958
and are practically begging you
to compete in the nationals!

468
00:21:46,541 --> 00:21:47,958
Yeah.

469
00:23:21,458 --> 00:23:23,500
♪

470
00:23:23,583 --> 00:23:26,541
The Odachi High
sumo club's Yuma Gojo.

471
00:23:26,625 --> 00:23:29,541
His henchmen are Hashi,
Funaki, and Saigo.

472
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:33,416
Dachi High's mascot
is Chanko the cat.

473
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:34,750
Very cute.

474
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:36,791
Um, Bro. Kinda creeper.

